      </div>
    
      <div class="hero-unit">
        <p><h2><a href="/blog/blog/simple-full-text-search-engine-for-repository-watchlist.html">Simple full-text search engine for repository watchlist</a></h2>02 Feb 2012 - 左左</p>
        <p>Many of you have been asking for this since the beginning. Today, I have the pleasure to announce that full-text search engine for your repository watchlist, is finally here. People who are watching several hundred of GitHub repositories like me, after login the first time, get a big list of untagged git projects and starting...</p>
        <p><a href="/blog/blog/simple-full-text-search-engine-for-repository-watchlist.html">Read more ...</a></p>
      </div>
    
      <div class="hero-unit">
        <p><h2><a href="/blog/blog/migrating-mongodb-between-cloud-based-providers.html">Migrating MongoDB between cloud-based providers</a></h2>25 Jan 2012 - 左左</p>
        <p>GitWatcher is an experimental platform currently based on Rails 3.1.3 and MongoDB/Mongoid, one of the most promising pairs of Object-Document-Mapper for NoSQL DBs, in the Ruby landscape. While the backend is on a cloud, the frontend is on another. Infact, the Rails app is running on Heroku Celadon Cedar Stack and the DB was initially...</p>
        <p><a href="/blog/blog/migrating-mongodb-between-cloud-based-providers.html">Read more ...</a></p>
      </div>
    
      <div class="hero-unit">
        <p><h2><a href="/blog/blog/gitWatcher-helps-you-to-stay-on-top-of-github-trending-projects.html">GitWatcher helps you to stay on top of github trending projects</a></h2>07 Jan 2012 - 左左</p>
        <p>Almost daily an interesting project appears on GitHub and you want to keep track of it because you know, sooner or later you will have to get ride of a similar problem in your own work. Then you hit the watch button and in a blink of eyes, your &quot;Watched Repositories&quot; list, grows to the...</p>
